cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on the development of a method for large-scale 3D reconstruction from consecutive monocular images, which is a problem commonly studied in the field of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves the use of a multi-task Convolutional Neural Network (CNN), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of semantic information, which is relevant to the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR).
